# How to make sure that Syntaxia main application has a consistent theme

Syntaxia applications must maintain a consistent terminal aesthetic with sharp, monospace styling.

- **Sharp Corners Only**
  - Never use `rounded`, `rounded-*` classes or CSS `border-radius`
  - All borders must have sharp edges for terminal aesthetic
  - Applies to buttons, inputs, containers, and all UI elements

- **Monospace Fonts Required**
  - Always use `font-mono` class on all text elements
  - Maintains terminal/code editor consistency
  - Essential for the technical brand identity

- **Consistent Button Sizing**
  - Standard height: `h-8` (32px)
  - Standard padding: `px-3 py-1`
  - Minimum width: `min-w-20` for consistency
  - Font size: `text-xs` for compact appearance

## Border Radius Rules

### ❌ DON'T: Use any border radius
```tsx
// WRONG - Never use these classes or styles
className="rounded"
className="rounded-md" 
className="rounded-lg"
style={{ borderRadius: '4px' }}
```

### ✅ DO: Keep all borders sharp
```tsx
// CORRECT - Sharp terminal-style borders
className="border border-terminal-green/30"
className="border border-terminal-green/30 px-3 py-1" // No rounded class
```

## Button Consistency Rules

### ❌ DON'T: Inconsistent button styling
```tsx
// WRONG - Mixing button styles
<button className="px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Button 1</button>
<button className="px-2 py-1 rounded">Button 2</button>
```

### ✅ DO: Consistent terminal button pattern
```tsx
// CORRECT - Standard terminal button pattern
<button className="font-mono text-xs bg-transparent border border-terminal-green/30 text-terminal-green hover:bg-terminal-green/10 hover:text-terminal-amber px-3 py-1 transition-colors h-8 min-w-20">
  ./action
</button>
```

## Form Element Rules

### ❌ DON'T: Rounded form inputs
```tsx
// WRONG - Rounded form elements
<input className="rounded-md border" />
<select className="rounded border" />
<textarea className="rounded-lg border" />
```

### ✅ DO: Sharp terminal-style inputs
```tsx
// CORRECT - Terminal-style form elements
<input className="border border-terminal-green/30 bg-background text-terminal-green font-mono px-3 py-2 focus:outline-none focus:border-terminal-green/50" />
```

## Component Consistency Requirements

### Button Standards
- **Height**: `h-8` (32px) for standard buttons
- **Padding**: `px-3 py-1` for horizontal/vertical spacing
- **Min-width**: `min-w-20` for consistency
- **Font**: `font-mono text-xs` for terminal aesthetic
- **Border**: `border border-terminal-green/30` with no radius

### Input Standards  
- **Font**: `font-mono` for monospace consistency
- **Colors**: `bg-background border-terminal-green/30 text-terminal-green`
- **Focus**: `focus:outline-none focus:border-terminal-green/50`
- **Padding**: `px-3 py-2` for proper spacing
- **No border radius**: Sharp edges only

### Color Palette
```tsx
// Terminal color variables (defined in global CSS)
--color-terminal-green    // Primary text and borders
--color-terminal-amber    // Hover states and accents  
--color-terminal-dark     // Background elements
```

