## Common Violations to Avoid

1. **Adding border radius anywhere** - Breaks terminal aesthetic
2. **Inconsistent button sizing** - Use standard h-8 height
3. **Missing monospace fonts** - All text should use font-mono
4. **Wrong color usage** - Stick to terminal color palette
5. **Inconsistent hover states** - Use standard terminal-green/amber pattern

## Validation Checklist

Before committing UI components, verify:

- [ ] No `rounded`, `rounded-*` classes used
- [ ] All interactive elements use `font-mono`
- [ ] Buttons follow standard sizing (`h-8`, `px-3 py-1`)
- [ ] Terminal color palette is used consistently
- [ ] Hover states use terminal-green/amber pattern
- [ ] All borders are sharp (no border-radius in CSS)


